Alibaba Group Holding (BABA.N) Price Target

Alicloud to further accelerate to \(30\% +\) and CMR to sustain at \(\sim 10\%\) in F2Q. Although we estimate QC loss to further widen to \(\sim \mathsf{Rmb}35\mathsf{bn}\) in F2Q (was Rmb20bn), this should mark the peak as management is committed to cut UE losses by half in the next 1- 2 months. Raise PT to US\\$165, reiterate SOTP US\\$200.

China's best AI enabler thesis playing out with cloud acceleration: Alicloud has delivered a solid \(26\%\) growth in 1Q beating market expectations, with AI contributing to \(20\% +\) of cloud revenue (among the highest globally). We expect Alicloud growth to accelerate in the coming quarters, thanks to strong industry demand, upgraded product offering (Qwen upgrade) and strategic partnerships (SAP). We estimate Alicloud \(+30\%\) in F2Q, with margins to remain stable at HSD%.

CMR growth to sustain at \(\sim 10\%\) despite a high base: CMR was \(+10\%\) in 1Q, driven by take rate improvement. We expect further penetration in site wide marketing tool (est. now \(30\%\) ) to further improve take rate, while quick commerce (QC) investments should further drive ad spend and traffic, supporting sustainable CMR growth. The company also highlighted QC can drive 2- 3ppt of incremental CMR growth in the next few quarters. We estimate CMR \(+10\%\) in F2Q, alleviating concerns over a high base from service fee implementation in Sep. last year.

QC loss to widen to Rmb35bn in F2Q; should mark the peak: We estimate investment in QC was \(\sim \mathsf{Rmb}11\mathsf{bn}\) in F1Q, while initial results have been encouraging, with peak daily order volume at 120mn (vs Meituan 150mn) and weekly daily avg. orders at 80mn in Aug. We expect QC loss to further expand to Rmb35bn in F2Q, (previously Rmb20bn given it is the summer season, which should mark the peak of investments. We expect FY QC investments at Rmb80bn (previously Rmb50bn). We expect BABAtostart focusing on non- food categories, which should further improve UE, while Management is committed to cut UE losses by half in the next 1- 2 months. BABA also said out incremental QC GMV target of Rmb1tn by F28. We estimate ecom EITA at Rmb11.8bn, \(- 73\%\) YoY and total EBITA of Rmb11.6bn, \(- 71\%\) YoY in F2Q.

Raise PT to US\\$165; reiterate SOTP US\\$200: We cut adjusted NP by 11% in F26 and 7% in F27 on widening QC investments but raise long- term estimates. We will monitor (1) QC volume vs UE trends, and (2) synergies with core business to evaluate the investment ROI. We remain confident in Alibaba being the primary CSP to capture rising AI- related demand. We reiterate our SOTP valuation at US\\$200 (raised cloud value to US\\$67 from US\\$60). Price target implies 15x F28 (assuming a normalized QC loss level).

Core business reacceleration and cloud growth driven by gen- Al adoption; OW

We expect Alibaba, having the largest cloud infrastructure in China, to win share in the current China evolutionary AI cycle. We see fundamental business reacceleration with improvement in monetization. The Internet regulatory environment appears to be easing; we view Alibaba as a key beneficiary as a China proxy. Our price target implies a target F2028e non- GAAP P/E of 15x. Strong cash flow- generating capabilities, dividends and continued share buybacks could provide downside support.
